               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; name of the protagonist; name of the church; incipit of Text I and of its sections; incipit of sections of Text II; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Simeon the Prophet feaures in some Ethiopic texts, like the Synaxarion with the commemorative notice dedicated to him for 8 Yäkkatit (s. ColSyn X, 58-61), in the Gädlä sämaʿtat, the homily for 8 Yäkkatit (s. EMML V, 345) or in the 4th and 5th Miracles of Jesus (s. GrébMJ I, 603-07), but no text comparable to Texts I-III have been identified so far, neither in Ethiopian published sources nor in CANT.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
